The functionality is very easy: it takes the most "fat" and the most "slim" brokers and finds a free-disk-space-gap between them. Then it swaps two partitions of these brokers so that the gap is maximally decreased.
The idea is that bubuku runs this functionality from time to time and keeps the size distribution among brokers more or less equal

